xes%20by%20giving%20stock%20and%20real%20estate%20to%20their%20parents%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222155%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Closeup%20low%20angle%20view%20of%20mid%2060's%20man%20and%20his%20son%20enjoying%20summer%20holiday%20on%20a%20sailboat.%20They%20are%20sitting%20on%20the%20deck%2C%20looking%20at%20the%20distance%2C%20talking%20and%20laughing.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F670961556ac7b701e7ca82f5%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221390%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EUpstream%20planning%20allows%20the%20rich%20to%20save%20on%20taxes%20while%20keeping%20assets%20in%20the%20family.%3Cp%3Egilaxia%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3ESelling%20appreciated%20assets%20like%20stock%20and%20real%20estate%20can%20trigger%20high%20capital%20gains%20taxes.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EMoguls%20can%20save%20big%20by%20gifting%20assets%20to%20their%20parents%2C%20inheriting%20them%20back%2C%20and%20then%20selling%20them.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EThe%20ultra-rich%20can%20use%20upstream%20transfers%20to%20double%20how%20much%20their%20kids%20inherit%20without%20estate%20tax.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EWealthy%20entrepreneurs%20face%20hefty%20capital%20gains%20taxes%20if%20they%20want%20to%20cash%20out%20after%20building%20a%20successful%20business%20from%20the%20ground%20up.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20if%20they%20are%20willing%20to%20wait%2C%20they%20can%20save%20big%20by%20gifting%20their%20stock%20to%20their%20parents%20and%20getting%20it%20back%20when%20they%20die.%20Capital%20gains%20tax%20applies%20to%20the%20appreciation%20between%20the%20sale%20price%20and%20the%20asset's%20cost%20basis%2C%20typically%20its%20purchase%20price.%20%26quot%3BUpstream%20transfers%26quot%3B%20take%20advantage%20of%20a%20tax%20loophole%20for%20inherited%20assets%20that%20boosts%20the%20cost%20basis%20to%20its%20fair%20market%20value%20at%20the%20time%20of%20inheritance.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20instance%2C%20a%20top%20earner%20looking%20to%20sell%20shares%20that%20had%20appreciated%20by%20%241%20million%20since%20they%20bought%20them%20would%20have%20to%20pay%20about%20%24238%2C000%20in%20taxes%2C%20according%20to%20Pam%20Lucina%2C%20chief%20fiduciary%20officer%20at%20Northern%20Trust.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20if%20they%20give%20the%20stock%20to%20their%20parents%20and%20sell%20it%20after%20inheriting%20it%2C%20they%20only%20have%20to%20pay%20that%2023.8%25%20tax%20rate%20on%20how%20much%20the%20stock%20had%20appreciated%20since%20their%20parents%20died%2C%20even%20if%20the%20stock%20had%20surged%20in%20value%20after%20they%20gave%20it%20away.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EYou%20get%20the%20most%20bang%20for%20your%20buck%20by%20choosing%20assets%20with%20a%20low%20cost%20basis%20relative%20to%20their%20current%20value.%20Publicly-held%20stock%2C%20real%20estate%2C%20and%20private%20business%20interests%20are%20popular%20choices%2C%20Lucina%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EUpstream%20planning%20is%20a%20powerful%20but%20risky%20tool%2C%20she%20told%20Business%20Insider.%20Individuals%20can%20lose%20their%20assets%20for%20good%20if%20their%20parents%20decide%20to%20share%20the%20wealth%20with%20a%20new%20spouse%20or%20other%20children.%20She%20estimates%20that%20only%20a%20quarter%20of%20clients%20actually%20go%20through%20with%20upstream%20planning%20after%20discussing%20it.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BOnce%20you%20talk%20through%20the%20risks%20and%20the%20family%20dynamics%20aspect%20of%20it%2C%20it%20doesn't%20work%20for%20every%20family%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThanks%20to%20tax%20cuts%20made%20during%20the%20Trump%20administration%2C%20individuals%20can%20gift%20or%20bequeath%20%2413.61%20million%20before%20triggering%20a%2040%25%20federal%20estate%20tax.%20The%20high%20exemption%20threshold%20has%20made%20upstream%20planning%20more%20popular.%20Lucina%20expects%20giving%20to%20pick%20up%20before%20the%20tax%20cuts%20expire%20at%20the%20end%20of%202025%2C%20barring%20action%20by%20Congress.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ERobert%20Strauss%2C%20partner%20at%20estate%20planning%20firm%20Weinstock%20Manion%2C%20typically%20uses%20upstream%20planning%20with%20ultra-rich%20clients%20who%20have%20already%20used%20their%20exemption%20but%20have%20less-wealthy%20parents%20who%20haven't.%20They%20can%20stash%20assets%20in%20a%20trust%20that%20benefits%20their%20parents%20until%20their%20passing%20and%20then%20the%20children.%20After%20the%20grandparents%20die%2C%20the%20children%20inherit%20the%20assets%20with%20a%20step-up%20basis.%20The%20federal%20estate%20tax%20doesn't%20kick%20in%20as%20long%20as%20the%20grandparents'%20estate%20does%20not%20exceed%20%2427.22%20million%2C%20the%20exemption%20for%20a%20married%20couple.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22fbe1dfa3-c1f3-49ff-b862-66a8fe0d22db%5C%22%3EBuyer%20beware%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Col%3E%3Cli%3E%3Cstrong%3EThe%20parents'%20creditors%20may%20have%20a%20right%20ot%20the%20assets.%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Fol%3E%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%20Lucina%2C%20the%20parents%20are%20usually%20given%20power%20of%20appointment%20over%20the%20assets%20to%20make%20sure%20they%20are%20included%20in%20their%20taxable%20estate.%20This%20legal%20right%20allows%20the%20parents%20to%20give%20or%20transfer%20the%20assets%20while%20they%20are%20alive.%20It%20also%20allows%20their%20creditors%20to%20pursue%20the%20assets%2C%20she%20warned.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Col%20start%3D%5C%222%5C%22%3E%3Cli%3E%3Cstrong%3EMake%20sure%20the%20whole%20family%20is%20on%20board.%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Fol%3E%3Cp%3ELucina%20said%20best-laid%20plans%20are%20more%20likely%20to%20fall%20apart%20when%20more%20people%20are%20involved%2C%20from%20siblings%20to%20spouses.%20For%20instance%2C%20the%20parents%20might%20change%20their%20minds%20about%20leaving%20a%20bigger%20inheritance%20to%20one%20child%2C%20even%20if%20that%20child%20gifted%20substantial%20assets%20to%20them.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOne%20of%20Lucina's%20clients%20had%20to%20promise%20to%20pay%20the%20parents'%20medical%20bills%20in%20order%20to%20get%20their%20siblings%20to%20agree%20to%20the%20arrangement.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFamily%20dynamics%20are%20the%20thorniest%20part%20of%20upstream%20planning.%20Strauss%20said%20it%20is%20important%20to%20be%20transparent%20with%20everyone%20involved%20before%20the%20upstream%20transfer.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BYou've%20got%20to%20navigate%20the%20family%20dynamics%20to%20make%20sure%20that%20an%20upstream%20actually%20isn't%20going%20to%20piss%20other%20people%20off%20or%20create%20an%20unrealistic%20expectation%20in%20an%20inheritance%20that's%20not%20intended%2C%26quot%3B%20Strauss%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Col%20start%3D%5C%223%5C%22%3E%3Cli%3E%3Cstrong%3EThe%20age%20of%20the%20parents%20is%20very%20important.%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Fol%3E%3Cp%3EWhile%20there%20is%20no%20hard%20and%20fast%20rule%2C%20Strauss%20typically%20uses%20upstream%20transfers%20when%20the%20wealth%20creator's%20parents%20are%20at%20least%20in%20their%20seventies%20or%20expected%20to%20live%20five%20more%20years%20or%20less.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt's%20a%20delicate%20balance.%20If%20the%20parents%20die%20within%20one%20year%20of%20the%20transfer%2C%20the%20assets%20do%20not%20receive%20a%20step%20up%20in%20basis.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20the%20assets%20are%20tied%20up%20during%20the%20parents'%20lifetime.%20During%20that%20time%2C%20the%20tax%20law%20and%20the%20value%20of%20the%20assets%20are%20bound%20to%20fluctuate.%20It%20is%20possible%20to%20unintentionally%20trigger%20estate%20taxes%20if%20the%20assets%20exceed%20the%20exemption%20amount%20by%20the%20time%20the%20parents%20die.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIdeally%2C%20what%20you're%20doing%20is%20you're%20targeting%20the%20exemption%20amount%20and%20not%20less%20and%20not%20more%2C%20but%20the%20value%20of%20the%20asset%20will%20change%20and%20the%20exemption%20amount%20will%20change%2C%26quot%3B%20Strauss%20said.%20%26quot%3BIt%20makes%20it%20harder%20to%20deal%20with.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20t