Url%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Here's%20how%20natural%20disasters%20are%20shaping%20the%20buy-versus-rent%20decision%20in%20vulnerable%20states%20like%20Florida%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222500%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22An%20aerial%20shot%20of%20hurricane%20damage%20in%20Florida.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F66fdaba57de5c8fd4834d08b%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221667%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EThe%20aftermath%20of%20Hurricane%20Helene%20in%20Horseshoe%20Beach%2C%20Florida.%3Cp%3ECHANDAN%20KHANNA%2FGetty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3EOwning%20a%20home%20in%20high-climate%20risk%20states%20like%20Florida%20is%20becoming%20tougher%20amid%20rising%20costs.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EStill%2C%20owning%20may%20be%20preferable%20as%20renters%20have%20significantly%20less%20policy%20support%20than%20homeowners.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EExperts%20say%20the%20next%20few%20years%20will%20be%20crucial%20for%20housing%20policy%20in%20the%20wake%20of%20severe%20climate%20disasters.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20states%20at%20high%20risk%20of%20climate-related%20events%2C%20both%20homeowners%20and%20renters%20face%20difficulties%20in%20the%20wake%20of%20natural%20disasters%2C%20but%20there%20are%20important%20things%20to%20consider%20in%20each%20case.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOn%20the%20one%20hand%2C%20buyers%20are%20facing%20rising%20costs%20as%20insurance%20premiums%20skyrocket.%20Renters%20could%20bear%20some%20of%20that%20burden%2C%20too%2C%20as%20rental%20properties%20face%20rising%20property%20insurance%20costs%20that%20could%20drive%20up%20rents%20in%20the%20future.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20when%20a%20natural%20disaster%20hits%2C%20like%20this%20week's%20Hurricane%20Milton%2C%20the%20stakes%20are%20different.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBoth%20renters%20and%20homebuyers%20face%20an%20immense%20loss%20of%20stability%20if%20their%20homes%20are%20damaged%20or%20destroyed%2C%20but%20homebuyers%20lose%20a%20huge%20investment.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHere%20are%20key%20factors%20at%20play%20when%20deciding%20to%20rent%20or%20to%20own%20a%20home%20in%20a%20state%20where%20climate%20risks%20are%20rising%20and%20natural%20disasters%20are%20becoming%20more%20frequent%20and%20destructive.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch3%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22fb983509-a634-4c57-8ea5-a41d41e6da00%5C%22%3EBoth%20renters%20and%20buyers%20face%20rising%20costs%3C%2Fh3%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20costs%20associated%20with%20owning%20a%20home%20are%20becoming%20more%20volatile%20as%20insurance%20costs%20rise%20due%20to%20climate%20risks.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThose%20dynamics%20really%20play%20more%20of%20a%20role%20in%20why%20you're%20seeing%20weaker%20markets%20right%20now%20in%20places%20like%20Texas%20and%20Florida%2C%20which%20see%20more%20severe%20storms%20and%20generally%20different%20forms%20of%20climate%20risk%2C%20and%20where%20homeowners%20are%20seeing%20greater%20increases%20in%20insurance%20premiums%2C%20which%20doesn't%20affect%20renters%20as%20much%2C%26quot%3B%20Redfin's%20head%20economist%2C%20Chen%20Zhao%2C%20told%20Business%20Insider.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAverage%20insurance%20premiums%20have%20increased%20sharply%20in%20the%20last%20few%20years%2C%20up%2033%25%20from%202020%20to%202023%2C%20but%20that%20trend%20is%20uneven%20depending%20on%20a%20state's%20natural%20disaster%20risk%2C%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.nber.org%2Fsystem%2Ffiles%2Fworking_papers%2Fw32579%2Fw32579.pdf%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EJune%20study%3C%2Fa%3E%20found.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EEven%20in%20regions%20in%20different%20states%20with%20similar%20climate%20risks%2C%20those%20in%20states%20with%20overall%20higher%20risks%20often%20bear%20a%20higher%20cost%20burden%20as%20insurers%20pay%20to%20transfer%20more%20risk%20to%20reinsurance%20companies.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFlorida%2C%20which%20has%20a%20reinsurance%20exposure%20of%20almost%2040%25%20due%20to%20high%20hurricane%20risk%20across%20the%20state%2C%20saw%20annual%20insurance%20premiums%20increase%20by%20about%20%241%2C000%20in%20zip%20codes%20close%20to%20its%20border%20with%20Georgia%2C%20even%20though%20areas%20on%20both%20sides%20of%20the%20border%20are%20similarly%20at%20risk.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EGeorgia%2C%20on%20the%20other%20hand%2C%20has%20less%20than%2010%25%20exposure%20to%20reinsurers%2C%20and%20its%20zip%20codes%20close%20to%20the%20border%20saw%20increases%20of%20less%20than%20%24500%20in%20the%20last%20few%20years.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOverall%2C%20rising%20disaster%20risk%20will%20raise%20annual%20premiums%20for%20climate-exposed%20households%20in%20the%20US%20by%20%24700%20by%202053%2C%20the%20study%20says.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20cost%20of%20owning%20a%20home%20also%20has%20been%20more%20volatile%20over%20time%20because%20of%20the%20rising%20insurance%20costs%20and%20the%20climate%20change%20impact%2C%20and%20also%20because%20home%20prices%20are%20going%20up%20so%20fast%2C%26quot%3B%20Jung%20Hyun%20Choi%2C%20a%20researcher%20at%20the%20Urban%20Institute's%20Housing%20Finance%20Policy%20Center%2C%20told%20Business%20Insider.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EStill%2C%20a%20big%20advantage%20to%20owning%20a%20home%20is%20the%20ability%20to%20lock%20in%20housing%20costs.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BHome%20ownership%20is%20still%20one%20of%20the%20most%20important%20ways%20of%20building%20wealth%20in%20this%20country%2C%26quot%3B%20Choi%20said%2C%20adding%20that%20not%20only%20do%20homeowners%20build%20equity%20over%20time%2C%20but%20their%20costs%20are%20often%20fixed%20via%20the%2030-year%20mortgage%2C%20which%20is%20the%20most%20popular%20home%20loan%20in%20the%20US.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ERenters%2C%20on%20the%20other%20hand%2C%20are%20subject%20to%20unpredictable%20price%20increases%20year-to-year.%20That's%20especially%20true%20after%20climate%20disasters%2C%20according%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fonlinelibrary.wiley.com%2Fdoi%2F10.1111%2Frisa.14224%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eone%20study%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20looked%20at%20rent%20prices%20following%20hurricanes%20in%20US%20coastal%20states.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20extreme%20disasters%2C%20median%20rents%20rise%20due%20to%20reduced%20housing%20supply.%20In%20less%20severe%20scenarios%2C%20rents%20may%20rise%20because%20building%20owners%20are%20trying%20to%20offset%20losses%20from%20property%20damage%2C%20or%20possibly%20take%20advantage%20of%20higher%20demand%20from%20displaced%20homeowners.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch3%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22ccd2411a-bab0-4107-bf3e-4c9ccc85ffbc%5C%22%3EPolicy%20favors%20homeowners%3C%2Fh3%3E%3Cp%3EWhile%20it%20may%20be%20tough%20to%20know%20whether%20costs%20for%20renters%20or%20buyers%20are%20more%20directly%20impacted%20after%20climate%20disasters%2C%20public%20policy%20is%20clearly%20skewed%20in%20favor%20of%20buyers%2C%20Choi%20says.%20She%20pointed%20to%20forbearance%20and%20loss%20mitigation%20policies%20that%20are%20meant%20to%20help%20buyers%20keep%20their%20homes.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAfter%20Hurricane%20Katrina%2C%2029%25%20of%20homes%20in%20Louisiana%20were%20damaged%2C%20compared%20with%2035%25%20of%20rental%20housing%20units%20%E2%80%94%20but%2062%25%20of%20damaged%20homes%20and%20only%2018%25%20of%20damaged%20rental%20units%20received%20disaster%20recovery%20assistance%2C%20according%20to%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.gao.gov%2Fproducts%2Fgao-10-17%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Efederal%20study%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20places%20where%20federal%20funding%20was%20implemented%20for%20renters%20after%20Hurricane%20Katrina%2C%20though%2C%20rents%20appreciated%20at%20a%20much%20slower%20rate%2C%20one%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.brookings.edu%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F09%2FDisasters-and-the-Rental-Housing_final.pdf%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Estudy%3C%2Fa%3E%20found%2C%20pointing%20to%20the%20potential%20for%20future%20policy%20to%20address%20renters'%20vulnerability%20to%20climate%20events.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EZhao%20points%20out%2C%20though%2C%20that%20renters%20generally%20have%20more%20flexibility%20to%20move%20and%20are%20less%20tied%20down%20when%20disasters%20strike.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BFor%20renters%2C%20it's%20a%20different%20story.%20You%20don't%20own%20the%20financial%20risk%20of%20living%20in%20Florida%20if%20a%20hurricane%20comes%20through%2C%26quot%3B%20Zhao%20said%2C%20adding%2C%20%26quot%3BI%20think%20that's%20the%20other%20thing%20that%20kind%20of%20drives%20a%20wedge%20between%20these%20regions%20and%20other%20places%20in%20the%20country%2C%20and%20also%20drives%20a%20wedge%20between%20homeowners%20and%20renters.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EZhao%20acknowledges%20that%20renters%20still%20%26quot%3Bcertainly%20own%20the%20personal%20risk%26quot%3B%20of%20a%20hurricane.%20Renters%20lose%20their%20housing%20stability%20personal%20property%20the%20same%20as%20homeowners.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhether%20renting%20or%20buying%20is%20more%20advantageous%20amid%20climate%20change%20will%20be%20determined%20by%20policy%20solutions%20implemented%20in%20the%20next%20few%20years.%20Unfortunately%2C%20there%20isn't%20a%20lot%20of%20clarity%20yet%2C%20Choi%20says.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EShe%20adds%20there's%20a%20chance%20that%20renting%20has%20the%20upper%20hand%20in%20high%20climate-risk%20areas.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIf%20we%20kind%20of%20leave%20it%20like%20this%2C%20it%20could%20be%20actually%20better%20to%20just%20rent%20because%20you%20don't%20really%20have%20to%20worry%20about%20your%20properties%20being%20severely%20damaged%20and%20you're%20not%20getting%20any%20insurance%20coverage%2C%26quot%3B%20Choi%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhurricane-milton-natural-disasters-buy-rent-florida-climate-change-risks-2024-10%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1728822661000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6706a448198738e3a70f5d86%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22h